Issues.Body:
- .NET Core Version: 5.0
- Does the bug reproduce also in WPF for .NET Framework 4.8?: N/A
- Is this bug related specifically to tooling in Visual Studio (e.g. XAML Designer, Code editing, etc...)? No

**Problem description:**
When a textbox receives focus, all of its text should be selected. (See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/660554/how-to-automatically-select-all-text-on-focus-in-wpf-textbox; there is a workaround event attached to PreviewMouseLeftButtonDown which prevents the events from bubbling to controls such as DataGrids for selecting the cell).

**Actual Behavior**
All text gets selected for a moment and is then deselected.

**Expected Behavior**
All text gets selected and stays selected.

**Minimal repro:**

1. Create a WPF project.
2. Put a textbox within the main window that is pre-populated with text
`<TextBox HorizontalAlignment="Left"
                 VerticalAlignment="Top"
                 Text="Select me" />`
3. Register a class handler in the App's OnStartup method that selects all text on focus

        protected override void OnStartup(StartupEventArgs e)
        {
            base.OnStartup(e);
            EventManager.RegisterClassHandler(typeof(TextBox), UIElement.GotFocusEvent, new RoutedEventHandler(TextBox_SelectAllText), true);
        }

        private void TextBox_SelectAllText(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
        {
            (sender as TextBox).SelectAll();
        }

4. Run the app and click on the TextBox
